[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* The expected output length is [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes more than the length of[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:   * the QNAME-encoding of the hostname.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:   * A valid DNS name may not contain a zero-length label, except at[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:   * the end. For this reason, a name beginning with a dot, or[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:   * containing a sequence of two or more consecutive dots, is invalid[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:   * and cannot be encoded as a QNAME.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:   * If the hostname ends with a trailing dot, the corresponding[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:   * QNAME-encoding is one byte longer than the hostname. If [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas is[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:   * also valid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the hostname is shortened by the omission of the[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:   * trailing dot, then its QNAME-encoding will be two bytes longer[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:   * than the hostname.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:   *[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:   * Each [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label, dot [0m[1;39m][0m[39m pair is encoded as [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m length, label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:   * preserving overall length. A final [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m without a dot is[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:   * also encoded as [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m length, label [0m[1;39m][0m[39m, increasing overall length[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:   * by one. The encoding is completed by appending a zero byte,[0m                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:   * the overall length by one.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:   *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m146[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdot[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:    else[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:      labellen = [0m[1;35mstrlen[0m[1;39m([0m[39mhostp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m150[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mlabellen > [0m[1;36m63[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!labellen[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m151[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* label is too long or too short, error out *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m152[0m[39m:      *olen = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1319[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mslot = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; slot < DOH_SLOT_COUNT; slot++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1320[0m[39m:      struct doh_probe *p = &dohp->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1321[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!p->dnstype[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1322[0m[39m:        continue;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1323[0m[39m:      rc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;35mdoh_resp_decode[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCurl_dyn_uptr[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&p->resp_body[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1324[0m[39m:                                 [0m[1;35mCurl_dyn_len[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&p->resp_body[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1325[0m[39m:                                 p->dnstype, &de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1326[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mCurl_dyn_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&p->resp_body[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1327[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_VERBOSE_STRINGS[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1328[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1329[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[32m"DoH: %s type %s for %s"[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mdoh_strerror[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1330[0m[39m:              [0m[1;35mdoh_type2name[0m[1;39m([0m[39mp->dnstype[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, dohp->host[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1331[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1332[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1333[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* next slot *[0m[35m/[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1334[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1335[0m[39m:    result = CURLE_COULDNT_RESOLVE_HOST; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* until we know better *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1336[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!rc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_IPV4[0m[1;39m][0m[39m || !rc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_IPV6[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1337[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* we have an address, of one kind or other *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1338[0m[39m:      struct Curl_dns_entry *dns;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1339[0m[39m:      struct Curl_addrinfo *ai;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1340[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1341[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1342[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCurl_trc_ft_is_verbose[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, &Curl_doh_trc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1343[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[32m"[0m[32m[[0m[32mDoH[0m[32m][0m[32m hostname: %s"[0m[39m, dohp->host[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1344[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mdoh_show[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, &de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1345[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1346[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1347[0m[39m:      result = [0m[1;35mdoh2ai[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de, dohp->host, dohp->port, &ai[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1348[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1349[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1350[0m[39m:        return result;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1333[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1339[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1333[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* next slot *[0m[35m/[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1334[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1335[0m[39m:    result = CURLE_COULDNT_RESOLVE_HOST; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* until we know better *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1336[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!rc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_IPV4[0m[1;39m][0m[39m || !rc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_IPV6[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1337[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* we have an address, of one kind or other *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1338[0m[39m:      struct Curl_dns_entry *dns;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1339[0m[39m:      struct Curl_addrinfo *ai;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1338[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1339[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1338[0m[39m:      struct Curl_dns_entry *dns;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1339[0m[39m:      struct Curl_addrinfo *ai;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:106[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m110[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root cause analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash in Curl_doh_close arises because `data->req.doh` is not set to NULL [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter it is freed by `Curl_doh_cleanup`. Later, when the request cleanup code [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invokes `Curl_doh_close` again, it dereferences a dangling [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer, leading to the wild read and SEGV.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key correction[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `lib/doh.c`, modify the `Curl_doh_cleanup` function to reset [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` to NULL immediately after freeing the struct. This ensures any [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent calls to `Curl_doh_close` will see `data->req.doh == NULL` and safely [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno-op.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed patch steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Open `lib/doh.c` and locate the `Curl_doh_cleanup` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. After the call to `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, insert `data->req.doh = [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL;`.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. The updated function should look like:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          data->req.doh = NULL;  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* prevent dangling pointer *[0m[35m/[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. No other changes are required. `Curl_doh_close` already safely checks [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why this fixes the issue[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By nullifying `data->req.doh` after free, any later invocations of [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor example from `Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will skip all probe cleanup [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic because the initial `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh && data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` check fails. This removes the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse-after-free scenario that ASan detected.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Preservation of existing functionality[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The only change is an additional pointer reset in cleanup. Existing DoH logic,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-handle cleanup, and error paths remain untouched. No harness, test code, or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal dependencies are modified.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests and fuzzing scenarios continue to exercise the same code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths; just the dangling-pointer case is prevented.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Side effects and mitigation[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no observable behavior change for normal DoH flows: cleanup still [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mruns once, and subsequent calls ignore any further cleanup attempts.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new memory is allocated or freed beyond the original design.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Code coverage for DoH cleanup remains the same, ensuring we don’t mask any [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreal resource leaks.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Reference to similar codebase patterns[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This follows the pattern used in other cleanup functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. in connection [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand DNS cleanup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where pointers are set to NULL after free to avoid double-free or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse-after-free errors.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/29/25 07:31:25][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=862441;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=298483;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m2[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.VULNERABLE[1m)[0m                                   [2m               [0m
[2;36m[12/29/25 07:32:27][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.ANALYZE -> TeamStatus.[1;33mPATCH[0m                     ]8;id=510921;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=466011;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately after freeing it in `lib/doh.c`. Despite the change, the fuzzer still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrashes at the same location and with an identical backtrace, showing that the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer issue at `Curl_doh_close` remains unresolved.[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- During a libFuzzer session, `curl_fuzzer_http` invokes a series of curl internal [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`multi_runsingle`, `curl_multi_perform`, `Curl_req_done`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m until it [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreaches `Curl_doh_close` in `lib/doh.c`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a SEGV at `doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[39m`, classifying it as a [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“wild-addr-read” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSCARINESS: [0m[1;36m20[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash is reproducible on the same test input over multiple runs, and the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbacktrace consistently ends in `Curl_doh_close` being called from `Curl_req_done` →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`multi_done`.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations in the Initial Log  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The invalid read occurs in `Curl_doh_close` at line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call chain is: Curl_doh_close → Curl_req_done → multi_done → multi_runsingle [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m→ curl_multi_perform → fuzz_handle_transfer.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No other AddressSanitizer diagnostics [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., heap-use-after-free[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are emitted, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly the raw SEGV.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `lib/doh.c`, immediately after:[0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  the following line was added:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    data->req.doh = NULL;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1440[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1441[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1442[0m[39m:#endif [0m[35m/[0m[39m* CURL_DISABLE_DOH *[0m[35m/[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1336[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1395[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1336[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!rc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_IPV4[0m[1;39m][0m[39m || !rc[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mDOH_SLOT_IPV6[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1344[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mdoh_show[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, &de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1354[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mCurl_share_lock[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, CURL_LOCK_DATA_DNS, CURL_LOCK_ACCESS_SINGLE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1363[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* returned failure, bail out nicely *[0m[35m/[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1364[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mCurl_freeaddrinfo[0m[1;39m([0m[39mai[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1366[0m[39m:      else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1367[0m[39m:        data->state.async.dns = dns;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1368[0m[39m:        *dnsp = dns;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1369[0m[39m:        result = CURLE_OK;      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* address resolution OK *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1370[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1371[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* address processing done *[0m[35m/[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1372[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1373[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Now process any build-specific attributes retrieved from DNS *[0m[35m/[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1374[0m[39m:#ifdef USE_HTTPSRR[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1375[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mde.numhttps_rrs > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && result == CURLE_OK && *dnsp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1376[0m[39m:      struct Curl_https_rrinfo *hrr = NULL;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1377[0m[39m:      result = [0m[1;35mdoh_resp_decode_httpsrr[0m[1;39m([0m[39mde.https_rrs->val, de.https_rrs->len,[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1378[0m[39m:                                       &hrr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1379[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mresult[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1380[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[32m"Failed to decode HTTPS RR"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1381[0m[39m:        return result;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1382[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1383[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[32m"Some HTTPS RR to process"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1384[0m[39m:# ifdef DEBUGBUILD[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1385[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mdoh_print_httpsrr[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, hrr[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1386[0m[39m:# endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1387[0m[39m:      [0m[1;39m([0m[39m*dnsp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m->hinfo = hrr;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1388[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1389[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1390[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1391[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* All done *[0m[35m/[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1392[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1393[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1394[0m[39m:    return result;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1395[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:125[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m130[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Can no longer [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m this struct as we need to keep some state *[0m[35m/[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m129[0m[39m:  req->size = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:  req->maxdownload = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Ensure all DoH resource frees nullify the pointer:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In lib/doh.c’s `Curl_doh_cleanup`, after `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, add [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh = NULL;`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This guarantees that any subsequent `Curl_doh_close` sees `data->req.doh == [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL` and immediately returns without dereferencing freed memory.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Guard against stale DoH pointers when resetting or aborting transfers:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In lib/request.c’s `Curl_req_hard_reset` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m125[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m130[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, after the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, explicitly set `data->req.doh = NULL;`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This handles the case where an easy handle is reused [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., by the fuzzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents a leftover pointer from triggering a wild read in the next [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` call.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Invoke cleanup on all early-exit paths in `Curl_doh_is_resolved`:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In lib/doh.c’s `Curl_doh_is_resolved` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m1336[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1395[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, lookup all [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`return result;` statements inside the `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!dohp->pending[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block _before_ the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinal cleanup call.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Prepend each of these early returns with:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that if DNS-to-AI conversion [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doh2ai`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m fails or HTTPS-RR [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecoding fails, we still free and nullify `data->req.doh`, preventing it from [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersisting in an uninitialized or partially populated state.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve existing logic and fuzzer harness compatibility:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All new pointer resets occur strictly within DoH and request-reset routines; [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwe do not touch any harness, fuzzing macros, or external dependencies.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The idempotent checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `Curl_doh_cleanup` and the newly added [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull assignments guarantee no functional change to successful DoH flows.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing lock/unlock sequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_share_lock/unlock`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `de_cleanup` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain intact to maintain thread safety and error reporting.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Mitigate side effects:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Calling `Curl_doh_cleanup` on every error path is safe because it checks for a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon-NULL `data->req.doh` and sequentially calls `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich is itself a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno-op if no multi handle or no probes remain[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then frees and nulls the pointer.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach mirrors cleanup patterns used elsewhere in curl [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., after [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHTTP/[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m streams[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, ensuring consistency.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After these fixes, any call to `Curl_req_done` → `Curl_doh_close` will never [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msee a dangling pointer, eliminating the wild read at doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410[0m[39m.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer-driven test on the curl codebase crashes with an AddressSanitizer SEGV [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min lib/doh.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The failure occurs during cleanup of [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDNS-over-HTTPS [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDOH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m state after fuzzed input processing. An attempted patch adds [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in error paths of `lib/doh.c` and nulls out [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` both there and after `Curl_doh_close` in `lib/request.c`. After [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the fuzzer still crashes in `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at a nearby [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msource line[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating the root issue remains unaddressed.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzer run on `curl_fuzzer_http` with a single testcase triggers a segmentation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfault within `Curl_doh_close`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash is a “wild-addr-read” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreading from a high, invalid address[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m reported [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby AddressSanitizer at `lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[39m`.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace excerpts:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Curl_doh_close → Curl_req_done → multi_done → multi_runsingle → [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcurl_multi_perform → fuzz_handle_transfer → LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput → fuzzer driver [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failure consistently reproduces under libFuzzer with [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m runs.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The invalid read happens inside the DOH cleanup routine, suggesting use of an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muninitialized or already-freed pointer.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `data->req.doh` appears to be freed or nulled incorrectly, leading to a stale [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreference in `Curl_doh_close`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzz_handle_transfer and LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m merely drives the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode and is not the root cause.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **lib/doh.c**  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On error paths after `doh2ai` failure and after HTTPS RR decode failure:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + Inserted `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` before each early `return result;`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - At the end of DOH cleanup, after freeing headers list:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + Set `data->req.doh = NULL;`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **lib/request.c**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwithin `Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, set [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh = NULL;`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReproduction Log After Patch  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer run commands and environment remain the same.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer now reports the crash at `lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1413:30[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthree lines below [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe original site, in the same function[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace is structurally identical, indicating `Curl_doh_close` is still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeing called with an invalid `data->req.doh`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The lifecycle and initialization of `data->req.doh`: ensure it is allocated [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore use and only freed once.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The internals of `Curl_doh_close` and `Curl_doh_cleanup`: check for repeated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrees or missing null-pointer guards.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call sites in `lib/request.c` and `lib/multi.c` that invoke `Curl_req_done` →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close`: verify ordering and detect any code paths that bypass the newly [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madded cleanup.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any conditional code that skips setting `data->req.doh` to NULL, allowing a stale[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer to persist.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interaction between `[0m[1;35mde_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&de[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: confirm [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect cleanup sequence and no double-free.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
