[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m348[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39m!is_multiplex && data->req.download_done[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || is_eos[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m349[0m[39m:      data->req.keepon &= ~KEEP_RECV;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m350[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m351[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* if we are PAUSEd or stopped receiving, leave the loop *[0m[35m/[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m352[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mk->keepon & KEEP_RECV_PAUSE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || ![0m[1;39m([0m[39mk->keepon & KEEP_RECV[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m353[0m[39m:      break;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m354[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m355[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxloops--[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m356[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m357[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mmaxloops <= [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mdata_pending[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m358[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* did not read until EAGAIN or there is still pending data, mark as[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m359[0m[39m:       read-again-please *[0m[35m/[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m360[0m[39m:    data->state.select_bits = CURL_CSELECT_IN;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1433[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1440[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1440[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:100[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m110[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m100:C[0m[39mURLcode [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:                       struct Curl_easy *data, bool aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mreq;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:125[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m130[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Can no longer [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m this struct as we need to keep some state *[0m[35m/[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m129[0m[39m:  req->size = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:  req->maxdownload = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The wild-address read occurs because Curl_req_done invokes Curl_doh_close on a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdangling `data->req.doh` pointer. After DOH operations [0m[1;39m([0m[39msuccessful or error[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh_probes` struct is freed but `data->req.doh` is never set to NULL. Subsequent [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls to Curl_doh_close see a non-NULL, freed pointer and dereference it.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Moreover, Curl_req_done only closes but never frees or clears `data->req.doh`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleaving stale state across multiple transfers on the same handle.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Insights from Code[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Curl_doh_cleanup correctly calls Curl_doh_close and frees the `doh_probes` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstruct, but omits `data->req.doh = NULL;` after freeing.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Curl_req_done and other request-finalization functions call Curl_doh_close [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectly instead of the full cleanup, so the struct is never freed in the normal [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequest path.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Curl_client_reset [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand req_flush[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m do not touch DOH state, so stale pointers [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersist across transfers.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Components[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Update Curl_doh_cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/doh.c[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, add `data->req.doh = NULL;`[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This change ensures that once the `doh_probes` struct is freed, the pointer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `data->req.doh` is cleared and cannot be used accidentally.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Replace Curl_doh_close with Curl_doh_cleanup in request teardown [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlib/request.c[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `Curl_req_done`, change:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In the secondary cleanup site [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe code after “req_hard_reset” or [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mequivalent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, replace the existing `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; data->req.doh = NULL;` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mfrom the previous patch attempt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a single `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Remove any manual `data->req.doh = NULL;` after Curl_doh_close calls since [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup will handle it.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Verify other cleanup paths[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `Curl_req_free` already calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, so no change is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeded there.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Error paths in lib/doh.c that invoke `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will now [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclear the pointer correctly.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. No changes to harness or test code.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In lib/doh.c, locate `Curl_doh_cleanup` and append `data->req.doh = NULL;` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately after the `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` line.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In lib/request.c, find all instances of `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` in request [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mteardown functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_req_done`, post-hard-reset, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and replace each with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Remove any residual lines setting `data->req.doh = NULL;` that followed [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirect calls to `Curl_doh_close`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Rebuild and rerun the libFuzzer harness to confirm the ASan SEGV no longer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By centralizing both close and free in `Curl_doh_cleanup` and ensuring it [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnulls out the pointer, we eliminate stale/dangling pointers.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replacing direct calls to `Curl_doh_close` with `Curl_doh_cleanup` in request [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mteardown guarantees that every DNS-over-HTTPS session is fully cleaned up, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing leftover state.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach preserves existing functionality: `Curl_doh_close` remains [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavailable internally for partial shutdowns, while end-of-request cleanup now [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly frees and nulls the probe state.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness, fuzzing logic, or external dependencies are modified, so existing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests and fuzzer entrypoints remain unchanged.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because `data->req.doh` is now always NULL after cleanup, any code erroneously[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpecting to inspect DOH state after request completion will see NULL. However, by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdesign, cleanup is final, and no such post-mortem inspection should occur.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No additional memory management side effects are expected; all [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocations/frees remain balanced.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Comprehensive existing tests for DOH functionality and multi-handle reuse [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be rerun to verify no regressions.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1433[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1440[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>lib/request.[0m[1;92mc:100[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m110[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>lib/request.[0m[1;92mc:125[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m130[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/29/25 07:37:15][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=905579;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=857044;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1406[0m[39m:    struct Curl_easy *probe_data;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1407[0m[39m:    curl_off_t mid;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1408[0m[39m:    size_t slot;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1409[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mslot = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; slot < DOH_SLOT_COUNT; slot++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1410[0m[39m:      mid = doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer crash is a use-after-free in `Curl_doh_close`: `data->req.doh` has [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeen freed elsewhere [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but never set to NULL, so [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_done`’s call to `Curl_doh_close` dereferences a dangling pointer.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing “cleanup” path [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m correctly frees the DoH [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext but did not guard against later calls to `Curl_doh_close` on the now-freed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patching only `Curl_doh_cleanup` to null out `data->req.doh` was insufficient,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbecause the HTTP/DoH teardown path invoked in-lib “close” [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_close`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m–and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot “cleanup”–so the nulling logic was never exercised in the fuzzer-triggered code[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Overview[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Centralize Post-Transfer DoH Teardown in `Curl_req_done` by using the proper [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“cleanup” function rather than the “close” helper.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Ensure that after freeing the `doh` context, `data->req.doh` is reset to NULL[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso that subsequent calls to `Curl_doh_close` are effectively no-ops.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Preserve all existing probe-slot logic in `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso ongoing DoH [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msessions continue to shut down correctly[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m while preventing double‐free or stale [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer dereference.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Patch Plan[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3.1[0m[39m. In lib/doh.c[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - Confirm [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor add, if missing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` nulls out `data->req.doh` after freeing.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - Example adjustment [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready applied in last patch attempt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            • After `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` insert `data->req.doh = NULL;`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - This guarantees that once `Curl_doh_cleanup` runs, `data->req.doh` == [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3.2[0m[39m. In lib/request.c[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - Locate the function `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m100[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - Replace the existing call to the lightweight close helper:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             from:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               #endif[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             to:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               #endif[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - This change causes every “request done” path to invoke the full cleanup [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mwhich both calls `Curl_doh_close` internally and then frees & nulls the `doh` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, rather than only calling `Curl_doh_close`.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Curl_doh_close` remains intact for internal probe shutdown, and its semantics[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare unchanged.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Curl_doh_cleanup` still calls `Curl_doh_close` first [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpreserving [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msocket/connection teardown[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then frees the slist and the `doh` struct, and now [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malso safely nulls the pointer.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness or fuzzing‐entry logic is altered; only core library code is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatched.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Addressing All Crashes[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By always freeing and nulling `data->req.doh` in the “request done” path, we [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate the dangling‐pointer scenario that triggered the wild read in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close`.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Subsequent calls to `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., double‐teardown[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will see [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh == NULL` and immediately return without dereferencing.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If users relied on inspecting `data->req.doh` after `Curl_req_done`, they will[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow find it NULL. This aligns with the expectation that the DoH context is torn [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdown after request completion.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Upstream code that adds additional DoH probes after a request would need to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecreate the context; this matches existing patterns where each transfer may [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecreate internal state.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests and harnesses continue to use the same API; no fuzzing [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflags, harness code, or utility functions are modified.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This single cohesive change eliminates the use-after-free by unifying the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mteardown path and ensuring that `data->req.doh` is reliably reset to NULL after [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfree. It covers all code paths without touching fuzzing or external dependencies.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1406[0m[39m:    struct Curl_easy *probe_data;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1407[0m[39m:    curl_off_t mid;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1408[0m[39m:    size_t slot;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1409[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mslot = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; slot < DOH_SLOT_COUNT; slot++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1410[0m[39m:      mid = doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1411[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1418[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1411[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmid < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1412[0m[39m:        continue;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1413[0m[39m:      doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1414[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* should have been called before data is removed from multi handle *[0m[35m/[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1415[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1416[0m[39m:      probe_data = data->multi ? [0m[1;35mCurl_multi_get_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m :[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1417[0m[39m:        NULL;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1418[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1439[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1432[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:100[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m108[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m100:C[0m[39mURLcode [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:                       struct Curl_easy *data, bool aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mreq;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The double‐free/memory‐use‐after‐free arises because `Curl_req_done` [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munconditionally invokes DOH teardown [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_close`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, even if[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe DOH context [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`data->req.doh`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was already cleaned up earlier in the DNS [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolution path.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After the first cleanup, `data->req.doh` becomes NULL [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor its memory is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. A subsequent call still enters `Curl_doh_close`, reading invalid memory and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggering the SEGV.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Simply converting the call in `Curl_req_done` from `Curl_doh_close` to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup` did not help: `Curl_doh_cleanup` itself calls `Curl_doh_close` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munconditionally when `data->req.doh` is non-NULL, but in some asynchronous code [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths `data->req.doh` is stale or non-NULL even after free.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Overview:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminate the redundant/unsafe DOH teardown in `Curl_req_done` by only [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoking DOH‐cleanup in one well‐defined place.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure `data->req.doh` is set to NULL immediately after any free—both in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup` and in all error/exiting paths.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Guard any invocation of `Curl_doh_close`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`Curl_doh_cleanup` with a check: only[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif `data->req.doh` is non-NULL and not already cleaned up.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Move the DOH teardown out of `Curl_req_done` entirely, since DOH cleanup is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready triggered at the end of the resolution/update state machine [0m[1;39m([0m[39min the multi [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when pending probes finish.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If the harness or any code path still expects DOH cleanup in `Curl_req_done` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor aborted requests, introduce a helper `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_check_and_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafely no‐ops if `data->req.doh` is NULL.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `lib/request.c`, revert the patch that calls `Curl_doh_cleanup` in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_done`. Instead:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Remove DOH cleanup call from `Curl_req_done` entirely.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Document in comments that DOH teardown is performed elsewhere.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If absolutely needed for aborted requests, wrap it in:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      But since `Curl_doh_cleanup` already checks for NULL, the unconditional call [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan stay[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      only if `data->req.doh` is never stale.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `lib/doh.c`, audit all paths that free `data->req.doh`:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, explicitly `data->req.doh = NULL;` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39malready done in `Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Locate any `goto error;` paths in `Curl_doh`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`doh_run_probe` that free or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbail out and ensure they nullify `data->req.doh`.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. In `Curl_doh_close` and `Curl_doh_cleanup`, add a defensive guard at function[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!data || !data->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to prevent operating on stale or freed pointers.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Add internal state tracking flag in `struct doh_probes` [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `bool [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleaned_up;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m set to false on allocation and true immediately before freeing. Then,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `Curl_doh_close`, check `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->cleaned_up[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;` to avoid re‐entry. [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFinally, set the flag in `Curl_doh_cleanup` before freeing.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Run existing test suite and fuzz harness to confirm no double‐free or SEGV.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Logic:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We keep existing DOH probe lifecycle: allocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, per‐slot [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_close`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, full cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By removing the spurious teardown in `Curl_req_done`, we avoid cleaning up [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore the multi‐handle loop is complete.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Defensive entry guards ensure no side‐effects if code paths accidentally call [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclose/cleanup twice.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new `cleaned_up` flag purely affects DOH internals and does not alter any [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpublic API or testable behavior.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Mitigation of Side Effects:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adding `cleaned_up` flag and entry guards has negligible performance cost and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes not change multi‐handle state.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removing the call in `Curl_req_done` must be validated against existing tests [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat expect DOH cleanup there. If any tests fail, wrap calls in `[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m…` instead of unconditional removal.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Comprehensive regression testing [0m[1;39m([0m[39munit tests + full test suite + fuzz runs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidate no regressions in HTTP, DOH, or multi‐perform.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Similar Patterns in Codebase:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The JSON and HTTP2 modules use similar “close then nullify” patterns guarded [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby internal flags to avoid multiple invocation. We mirror that robust pattern for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDOH.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Many other curl cleanup routines [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `Curl_ftp_disconnect`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m use early‐exit [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguards; applying the same pattern here brings consistency.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Summary:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminate redundant DOH cleanup call from `Curl_req_done`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Harden `Curl_doh_close`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`Curl_doh_cleanup` with entry guards and internal [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstate flag.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure pointer nullification on all free paths.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validate by regression and fuzz testing.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis strategy resolves the SEGV by avoiding use‐after‐free of the DOH context, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserves all intended behavior, and aligns with curl’s cleanup idioms.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
